                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/113</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-29T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1915, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Silliman suggests commission representing banking interests should meet General
                    Carranza to explain grievances, adding he could arrange meeting. He thinks Mr.
                    Nieto should be present at meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
